By Mustapha Yauri Abuja – The Federal Government has renewed the appointment of Dr Dennis Allagoa as the Medical Director, Federal Medical Centre, Yenagoa, Bayelsa, for a second and final term of four years. A statement issued by Mrs Boade Akinola, Director Media and Public
Relations, Federal Ministry of Health, on Saturday in Abuja, said the
re-appointment was with effect from March 11. The statement quoted the Minister of State for Health, Dr Osagie Ehanire,congratulating Allagoa on his renewed appointment. It said Ehanire enjoined Allagoa to do his best at improving on the
achievements already attained at the hospital and justify the confidence
reposed on him by President Muhammadu Buhari through his
re-appointment. It added that the minister advised Allagoa to focus more on service
performance in order to build public trust in the health sector. The statement said Ehanire noted that the facility could build public
trust by treating patients with respect and diligent service delivery. It said that the minister further charged the Medical Director to
work in harmony with all stakeholders in the sector and in support of
Buhari’s change agenda.